    stable 2.3.3 2.3.2 2.3.0 2.2.6 2.2.0
   require id3 cd-discid id3v2
  optional cdparanoia   '' '' to rip CDs
  optional cdrtools     '' '' to rip CDs using cdda2wav
  optional lame         '' '' to encode mp3 files
  optional vorbis-tools '' '' to encode ogg vorbis files
  optional flac         '' '' to encode flac files
  optional normalize    '' '' for volume normalization
  optional distmp3      '' '' for distributed mp3 encoding
#optional bladeenc    '' '' to encode mp3 files

    ignore '\-1'
  category audio/cd
 attribute console
    source abcde_$VERSION.orig.tar.gz
  homepage http://www.hispalinux.es/~data/abcde.php
       url http://www.hispalinux.es/~data/files/
  estimate 5
      desc 'abcde is A Better CD encoder

abcde is a frontend to cdparanoia, wget, cd-discid, id3,
and your favorite Ogg/MP3 encoder (Oggenc is the default).
It grabs an entire CD and converts each track to Ogg/MP3,
then comments or ID3-tags each file, all with one command.
It supports parallelization, SMP, HTTP proxies,
customizable filename organization and munging,
playlist generation, and remote distributed encoding via distmp3.

Copy /etc/abcde.conf to ~/.abcde.conf and edit
it to suit your needs before running the program.'


build(){
prepare_install &&
make    install
}
